  <Name>k__BackingField: Hosea
  fancyName: 
  nickname: hos
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Commands Hosea to Start a Family'
      title: God Commands Hosea to Start a Family
      number: 1
      content: 'The word of Yahweh that came to Hosea son of Beeri, in the days of
        Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, the kings of Judah, and in the days of
        Jeroboam the son of Joash, king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "At the beginning when Yahweh spoke through Hosea, Yahweh said to
        Hosea, \u201CGo, take for yourself a wife and children of whoredom, because
        the land commits great whoredom forsaking Yahweh.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So he went and took Gomer daughter of Diblaim, and she conceived
        and bore him a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Yahweh said to him, \u201CName him Jezreel;  because in a little
        while I will punish the house of Jehu  for the blood of Jezreel,  and I will
        put an end to the kingdom of the house of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "On that day  I will break the bow of Israel in the Valley of Jezreel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And she conceived again and bore a daughter, and he said to him,
        \u201CName her Lo-ruhamah,  for I will no longer have pity on the house of
        Israel or forgive them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But I will have pity on the house of Judah and I will save them by
        Yahweh their God, and will not deliver them by bow, sword, war, horses, or
        horsemen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And when she had weaned Lo-ruhamah, she conceived and bore a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he said, \u201CName him Lo-ammi,  for you are not my people and
        I am not your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: " The number of the children of Israel will be like the sand of the
        sea that cannot be measured or counted; and in the place where it is said
        to them, \u201CYou are not my people,\u201D it will be said to them, \u201CChildren
        of the living God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the children of Judah and Israel will be gathered together,
        and they will appoint for themselves one head; and they will take possession
        of the land, for great is the day of Jezreel.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Unfaithful Wife'
      title: The Unfaithful Wife
      number: 1
      content: "Say to your brother, \u201CAmmi,\u201D  and to your sister, \u201CRuhamah.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Plead with your mother, plead\u2014 because she is not my wife, and
        I am not her husband. Let her put away her whoring from before her,  and
        her adultery from between her breasts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Lest I strip her naked and expose her like the day when she was born;
        I will make her like the desert and turn her into parched land; I will kill
        her with thirst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And I will not have pity on her children, because they are children
        of whoredom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Because their mother was unfaithful;  she who conceived them has
        acted shamefully, for she said: \u201CI will go after my lovers, the ones
        who give me my bread, my water, my wool, and my flax, my oil, and my drink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore, Look! I am going to hedge her path with thorns,  and I
        will build a stone wall, a stone wall against her, and she will not find
        her paths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then she will pursue her lovers,  but she will not overtake them;
        she will seek them and not find them; and she will say, \u201CI will go and
        return to my first husband because it was better for me then than now.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But she did not know that it was I who gave her grain, new wine,
        and oil, and who gave her silver in abundance, and gold which they made into
        a Baal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore I will take again my grain in its time, and my wine in
        its season; and I will take away my wool and my flax, which were to cover
        her nakedness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And now I will uncover her nakedness before the eyes of her lovers,
        and no one will rescue her from my hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And I will put an end to all her mirth, her festivals, her new moons,
        and her Sabbaths,  and all her appointed festivals;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "and I will lay waste to her vines and her fig trees,  of which she
        said, \u201CThey are my payment for prostitution, which my lovers gave to
        me.\u201D I will make them a forest, and the wild animals of the field will
        devour them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I will punish her for the days of the Baals, to whom she burns incense,
        and she decked herself with her ornamental ring and jewelry, and she went
        after her lovers, and forgot me \u2014a declaration of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore, Look! I am going to allure her and bring her into the
        desert, and I will speak tenderly to her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'From there I will give her her vineyards, and the Valley of Achor
        as a doorway of hope. And there she will respond, as in the days of her youth,
        just as in the day of her coming out of the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And on that day\u2014  a declaration of Yahweh\u2014 you will call
        me, \u201CMy husband;\u201D  you will no longer call me, \u201CMy Baal.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I will remove the names of the Baals from her mouth, and they will
        no longer be mentioned by their name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I will make a covenant for them on that day, with the animals of
        the field, with the birds of the heaven, and with the creeping things of
        the ground; the bow, the sword, and the war I will abolish from the land,
        and I will let them lie down in safety. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And I will take you as my wife forever; I will take you as a wife
        for myself in righteousness and in justice, in steadfast love and in mercy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I will take you as my wife in faithfulness, and you will know Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'On that day I will answer, declares Yahweh,  I will answer the heavens,
        and they will answer the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the earth will answer the grain, the wine, and the oil, and they
        will answer Jezreel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "I will sow her for myself in the land; I will have pity on Lo-ruhama; 
        I will say to Lo-ammi,  \u201CYou are my people,\u201D and he himself will
        say, \u201Cyou are my God.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Another Symbolic Marriage'
      title: Another Symbolic Marriage
      number: 1
      content: "And Yahweh said to me again, \u201CGo, love a woman who has a lover
        and is committing adultery, just like the love of Yahweh for the children
        of Israel, but they are turning to other gods and love raisin cakes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I bought her for fifteen shekels of silver and a homer of barely
        and a measure of wine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And I said to her, \u201CYou must remain as mine for many days, and
        you will not play the whore; you will not belong to a man, and I will belong
        to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The children of Israel will remain for many days without a king and
        prince, without sacrifice and stone pillar, ephod and teraphim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Afterward the children of Israel will return and seek Yahweh their
        God and David their king. They will come in fear to Yahweh and to his goodness
        at the end of days. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Yahweh Has an Indictment'
      title: Yahweh Has an Indictment
      number: 1
      content: 'Hear the word of Yahweh, O children of Israel, for Yahweh has an
        indictment against the inhabitants of the land. There is no faithfulness
        or loyalty, there is no knowledge of God in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Swearing and lying, murdering and stealing, and adultery break out, 
        and bloodshed follows bloodshed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore the land mourns, and all those living in it languish with
        the animals of the field, and the birds of the heaven, and even the fish
        of the sea are being swept away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Yet, let no one contend, and let no one accuse, for with you, O priest,
        is my contention.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You will stumble by day, and the priest also will stumble with you
        at night. And I will destroy your mother; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'My people are destroyed for lack of knowledge; because you have rejected
        knowledge, I reject you from acting as a priest for me.  And since you have
        forgotten the law of your God, I will also forget your children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When they became many, their sin increased against me; they changed
        their glory into shame. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They feed on the sin of my people,  they are greedy for their iniquity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And it will be like people, like priest; I will punish them for their
        ways, and I will requite them for their deeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They will eat and not be satisfied; they will play the whore and
        not multiply, because they have forsaken Yahweh to devote themselves to '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'whoredom.  Wine and new wine take away the understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'My people, consult their wooden idols,  and their divining rod gives
        them oracles; because a spirit of whoredom led them astray, and they played
        the whore from under their God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'On the tops of the mountains they sacrifice, and on the hills they
        make offerings, under oak, poplar, and terebinth, because their shade is
        good. Therefore your daughters play the whore, and all your daughters-in-law
        commit adultery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will not punish your daughters when they play the whore, or your
        daughters-in-law when they commit adultery; because they go aside with whores,
        and they sacrifice with temple prostitutes, a people that does not understand
        comes to ruin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Even though you, O Israel, are playing the whore, do not let Judah
        become guilty; do not enter Gilgal, or go up to Beth-aven; and do not swear,
        \u201CAs Yahweh lives!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Indeed, like a stubborn heifer, Israel is stubborn; Now Yahweh will
        feed them, like a lamb in broad pasture.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Ephraim is joined to idols; let him alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When their drinking has ended, they surely indulge in sexual orgies.
        They love lewdness more than their glory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'A wind has wrapped them in its wings, and they will be ashamed because
        of their altars. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Priests Are a Snare'
      title: The Priests Are a Snare
      number: 1
      content: 'Hear this, O priests! Give heed, O house of Israel! Listen, O house
        of the king! Because the judgment applies to you; because you have been a
        snare for Mizpah, and a net spread out on Tabor; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'they dug a deep pit in Shittim, but I am a punishment for all of
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I myself know Ephraim, and Israel is not hidden from me; because
        now you have played the whore, O Ephraim\u2014 Israel is defiled. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Their deeds do not permit them to return them to God. Because a spirit
        of whoredom is in their midst, they do not know Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The pride of Israel testifies against him,  and Israel and Ephraim
        stumble in their guilt, and Judah stumbles with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'With their flocks and herds they will go to seek Yahweh, but they
        will not find him; he has withdrawn from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They have dealt faithlessly with Yahweh because they have borne illegitimate
        children. Now the new moon will devour them with their fields. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Blow the horn in Gibeah, the trumpet in Ramah. Sound the alarm in
        Beth-aven; look behind you, Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ephraim will be a desolation in the day of punishment; among the
        tribes of Israel I will reveal what is true. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The princes of Judah have become like those who remove a landmark;
        on them I will pour out my wrath like water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Ephraim is oppressed, crushed in judgment, because he was determined
        to go after filth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But I am like a maggot to Ephraim and like rottenness to the house
        of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And when Ephraim saw his illness, and Judah his wound, Ephraim went
        to Assyria, he sent to the great king.  But he was unable to cure you and
        heal your wound. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Because I will be like a lion to Ephraim and like a fierce strong
        lion to the house of Judah. I myself will tear and I will go; I will carry
        off, and there is no one who delivers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I will return again to my place until they acknowledge their guilt
        and seek my face; in their distress they will search me. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Call to Yahweh'
      title: A Call to Yahweh
      number: 1
      content: 'Come, let us return to Yahweh; because it is he who has torn, and
        he will heal us; he has struck us down and will bind us up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He will revive us after two days; on the third day he will raise
        us up, that we may live in his presence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Let us know, let us press on to know Yahweh; his rising is sure like
        the dawn. He will come like the showers to us, like the spring rain that
        waters the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'What will I do with you, O Ephraim? What will I do with you, O Judah?
        Your love is like a morning cloud, like the dew that goes away early in the
        morning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore, I have hewn them by the prophets; I have killed them by
        the words of my mouth, and my judgment goes forth like the light. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Because I desire steadfast love and not sacrifice, and knowledge
        of God rather than burnt offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But like Adam, they transgressed the covenant; there they dealt faithlessly
        with me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Gilead is a city of evil, a cunning city because of blood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Like bandits lying in wait, so is a band of priests; they murder
        on the road to Shechem; indeed, they commit a monstrous crime. '
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Ephraim\u2019s Guilt"
      title: "Ephraim\u2019s Guilt"
      number: 10
      content: "In the house of Israel I have seen something horrible; Ephraim\u2019s
        unfaithfulness is there. Israel is defiled. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For you also, O Judah, a harvest is appointed, when I restore the
        fortunes of my people, '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: ' when I would heal Israel, and the corruption of Ephraim is revealed,
        and the wicked deeds of Samaria; because they deal in falsehood, the thief
        breaks in,  and the bandit raids the outside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But they did not consider  that I remember all their wickedness.
        Now their deeds surround them; they are before my face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'By their wickedness they make the king glad, and the officials by
        their treacheries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'All of them commit adultery, like a burning oven whose baker has
        stopped from stirring the fire, and from kneading the dough until it is leavened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'On the day of our king, the princes became sick with the heat of
        wine;  he stretched out his hand with mockers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Because they are kindled like an oven, their heart burns within them;
        all night their anger smolders,  in the morning it blazes like a flaming
        fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All of them are hot as an oven, and they devour their rulers. All
        their kings have fallen; there is none who calls to me amongst them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ephraim mixes himself with the nations; Ephraim is a bread cake not
        turned over. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Foreigners devour his strength, and he does not know it; mold is
        also sprinkled upon him, and he does not know it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The pride of Israel testifies against him\u2014 they do not return
        to Yahweh their God; they do not seek him for all of this.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Ephraim was like a dove, silly, without sense;  they call to Egypt,
        they go to Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Just as they go, I will cast my net over them; I will bring them
        down like the birds of the heavens;  I will discipline them according to
        a report to their assembly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Woe to them, because they have strayed from me! Destruction to them,
        because they have rebelled against me! I myself would redeem them, but they
        speak lies against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They do not cry out to me from their heart, but they wail on their
        beds; because of grain and new wine they lacerate themselves; they depart
        from me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And I myself trained and strengthened their arms; but they plan evil
        against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They turn, not to the Most High,  like a slack bow; their officials
        will fall by the sword because of the anger of their tongue. This is their
        scorn  in the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Rejects the Good'
      title: Israel Rejects the Good
      number: 1
      content: 'Put to your lips the trumpet like a vulture over the house of Yahweh,
        because they have broken my covenant  and rebelled against my law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "They cry out to me, \u201CMy God! We, Israel, know you!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Israel has spurned the good; the enemy will pursue him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They appointed kings, but not through me; they made officials, but
        without my knowledge. With their silver and gold they made idols for themselves
        for their own destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Your calf is rejected, O Samaria; my anger burns against them. How
        long will they be incapable of innocence? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Because it is from Israel, an artisan made it, it is not a god; for
        the calf of Samaria will be broken to pieces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Because they sow the wind, they will reap the whirlwind. The standing
        grain does not have heads;  it will not yield flour. And if it would yield,
        strangers would devour it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Israel is swallowed up; now they are among the nations, like an object
        that no one desires. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For they have gone up to Assyria, a wild donkey alone to itself;
        Ephraim has sold itself for lovers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Even though they have sold themselves to the nations, now I will
        gather them. They will soon writhe from the burden of kings and princes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When Ephraim multiplied altars to expiate sins, they became to him
        altars to sin on. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I write for him myriads of my instruction;  they are regarded as
        a strange thing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They offer sacrifices of my choice  and they eat flesh; Yahweh does
        not accept them. Now he will remember their iniquity and punish their sins;
        they will return to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Israel has forgotten his maker and built palaces, and Judah has multiplied
        fortified cities; but I will send fire on his cities and it will devour her
        strongholds. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ephraim Faces Punishment'
      title: Ephraim Faces Punishment
      number: 1
      content: "Do not rejoice, O Israel, do not exult like the nations! For you
        played the whore, departing from your God; you loved a harlot\u2019s wage
        on all the threshing floors of grain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Threshing floor and wine vat will not feed them, and new wine will
        fail her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They will not remain in the land of Yahweh. But Ephraim will return
        to Egypt, and in Assyria they will eat unclean food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They will not pour drink offerings of wine to Yahweh, and their sacrifices
        will not please him. They are like mourners\u2019 bread for them; all those
        who eat it will be defiled. For their bread will be for their hunger;  it
        will not come to the house of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'What will you do on the day of the appointed time, and on the day
        of the festival of Yahweh? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For look! If they flee from the destruction, Egypt will gather them;
        Memphis will bury them. Nettles will possess their precious things of silver;
        thorns will be in their tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The days of punishment have come; the days of retribution have come;
        Israel knows! The prophet is a fool, the man of the spirit is acting like
        a madman. Because of the greatness of your sin, your hostility is great. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The prophet keeps watch over Ephraim for my God; the snare of a fowler
        is on all his ways, and hostility in the house of his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They deeply corrupted themselves  as in the days of Gibeah; he will
        remember their sin, he will punish their sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Like the grapes in the wilderness, I found Israel. Like early ripened
        fruit on the fig tree in the first season,  I saw your ancestors.  They themselves
        came to Baal Peor, and they consecrated themselves to shame. And they became
        detestable things, like the thing they love.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Ephraim\u2019s glory is like a bird; it will fly away\u2014 no birth,
        no pregnancy, and no conception. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Even though they bring up their children, I will bereave them before
        maturity.  Woe to them indeed, when I depart from them! '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Ephraim, as I see it, is like a palm in a meadow; but Ephraim must
        bring out his children to the slayer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Give them, O Yahweh\u2014 what will you give them? Give them a miscarrying
        womb and dry breasts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Every evil of theirs began at Gilgal, so I began to hate them there;
        because of the evil of their deeds I will drive them out from my house. I
        will love them no more; all their officials are rebels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Ephraim is stricken, their root is dried up, they shall not bear
        fruit. Even if they give birth, I will kill the cherished offspring of their
        womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'My God will reject them because they did not listen to him, and they
        will be wanderers among the nations. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Is Punished'
      title: Israel Is Punished
      number: 1
      content: 'Israel is a luxuriant vine;  he yields fruit for himself. The more
        his fruit increased, the more he made numerous altars. The more his land
        prospered, the more he improved his stone pillars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Their heart is false; now they must bear their guilt. He himself
        will break down their altars; he will destroy their stone pillars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For now they will say, \u201CWe have no king; indeed, we did not
        fear Yahweh, and what can a king do for us?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They utter words of vain oaths when making covenants,  and judgment
        blossoms like a poisonous plant on the furrows of the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The inhabitants of Samaria tremble for the calf of Beth-aven. Indeed,
        his people will mourn for it, and his idolatrous priests will wail over it\u2014
        over its glory because it has departed from it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'It will also be brought to Assyria, as tribute to the great king. 
        Ephraim will obtain disgrace and Israel will be ashamed from his advice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Samaria will be destroyed; her king is like a chip on the surface
        of the water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The high places of Aven, the sin of Israel, will be destroyed. Thorn
        and thistle will grow on their altars. They will say to the mountains, \u201CCover
        us,\u201D and to the hills, \u201CFall on us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'From the days of Gibeah you have sinned, O Israel; there they have
        remained.  Will not war in Gibeah overtake them against the children of evil? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In my desire I will punish them; nations will be gathered against
        them when they are punished for their double iniquities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Ephraim was a trained heifer, that loved to thresh grain, and I myself
        spared  the fairness of her neck; I will make Ephraim break the ground, Judah
        will plow, Jacob must till for himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Sow for yourselves righteousness; reap loyal love.  Break up for
        yourself fallow ground; it is time to seek Yahweh so he will come and rain
        righteousness upon you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You have plowed wickedness, you have reaped injustice, you have eaten
        the fruit of lies,  because you have trusted in your strength, in the multitude
        of your warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The tumult of war will rise up against your people, and all your
        fortresses will be destroyed, as Shalman destroyed Beth-arbel; on the day
        of war mothers were dashed to pieces with their children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So it will be done to you, O Bethel, because of the evil of your
        wickedness; at dawn, the king of Israel will be utterly destroyed. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Will Have Compassion'
      title: God Will Have Compassion
      number: 1
      content: 'When Israel was a child, I loved him, and out of Egypt I called my
        son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When I called them, they went from my face.  They sacrificed to the
        Baals, and they sacrificed to idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And I myself taught Ephraim to walk; I took them in my arms, but
        they did not know that I healed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I drew them with human ties,  with the bands of love. I was to them
        like one who lifted up a yoke on their jaws,  though I bent down to them
        and let them eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He will return to the land of Egypt, and Assyria will be his king, 
        because they refused to return. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sword rages in his cities; it consumes his false prophets and
        devours because of their plans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'My people are bent on backsliding from me. To the Most High they
        call, he does not raise them at all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'How can I give you up, O Ephraim? How can I hand you over, O Israel?
        How can I make you like Admah? How can I treat you like Zeboiim? My heart
        is disturbed within me; all my compassions are aroused. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will not execute my fierce anger,  I will not again destroy Ephraim;
        because I am God and not a mortal,  the Holy One in your midst; and I will
        not come in wrath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They will go after Yahweh; he roars like a lion. When he roars, his
        children will come trembling from the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "11: Israel\u2019s History"
      title: "Israel\u2019s History"
      number: 11
      content: "They will tremble like birds from Egypt, and like doves from the
        land of Assyria; and I will let them return to their homes\u2014 a declaration
        of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: ' Ephraim has surrounded me with lies,  and the house of Israel with
        deceit; and Judah is still wandering with God and is faithful to the Holy
        One. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: ' Ephraim herds the wind  and is pursuing the east wind all day long;
        he multiplies deception and violence and he makes a treaty with Assyria, 
        and oil is brought to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Yahweh has a quarrel with Judah and will punish Jacob according to
        his ways and repay him according to his deeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In the womb he deceived his brother, and in his manhood he struggled
        with God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He struggled with the angel and prevailed; he pleaded for his mercy.
        He met him at Bethel, and there he spoke with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Yahweh the God of hosts, Yahweh is his renowned name! '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But you, you must return to your God; keep love and justice, and
        wait continually for your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The trader, in his hand are scales of deceit;  he loves to oppress. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Ephraim said, \u201CSurely, I am rich, I gained wealth for myself;
        in all my toil they have not found guilt in me that is sin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But I am Yahweh your God since the land of Egypt; I will make you
        live in tents again, like the days of the appointed festival. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I spoke to the prophets; I myself multiplied revelations  and through
        the hand of the prophets I will destroy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'If in Gilead there is evil, surely they will come to nothing. In
        Gilgal they sacrifice bulls, also their altars will be like stone heaps on
        furrows of the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Jacob fled to the open field of Aram,  and Israel served for a wife,
        and for a wife he watched over sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And by a prophet Yahweh brought Israel up from Egypt, and by a prophet
        he was watched over. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Ephraim has caused bitter provocation, and his Lord will hold him
        responsible for his crimes  and pay back to him his insults. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Yahweh\u2019s Judgment on Idolatrous Israel"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Judgment on Idolatrous Israel"
      number: 1
      content: 'When Ephraim spoke, there was terror; he was exalted in Israel, but
        he incurred guilt through Baal and died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And now they sin again, and they make for themselves a molten idol,
        idols from their silver metal according to their understanding, all of them
        the work of skilled craftsmen. To these they say, \u201CSacrifice!\u201D
        People are kissing bull calves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore, they will be like the morning cloud, and like the dew
        of early morning going away, like chaff swirling from the threshing floor,
        or like smoke from a window. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I am Yahweh your God since the land of Egypt; you know no god except
        me, and no one saves besides me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I fed you in the desert, in the land of drought. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When I fed them, they were satisfied; they were satisfied and their
        heart was lifted up; therefore they forgot me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I will be like a lion to them; I lie in wait beside the way,
        like a leopard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will attack them like a bear robbed of her offspring, and I will
        tear open the covering of their heart; there I will devour them like a lion,
        like an animal of the field would mutilate them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will destroy you, O Israel; who will help you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Where now is your king that he may save you? Where in all your cities
        are your judges, of whom you said, \u201CGive to me a king and rulers?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I gave you a king in my anger, and I took him in my wrath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The sin of Ephraim is wrapped up; his sin is concealed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The labor pains of childbirth come for him; he is an unwise son because
        at the proper time, he does not present himself at the mouth of the womb.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Should I redeem them from the power of Sheol?   Should I deliver
        them from death? Where are your plagues, O Death? Where is your destruction,
        O Sheol?  Compassion is hidden from my eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Although he may flourish among reeds,  the east wind will come, a
        wind of Yahweh rising from the desert; his fountain will dry up, his spring
        will be parched. It will plunder his treasury,  every object of desire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: ' Samaria will be guilty, because she has rebelled against her God;
        they will fall by the sword, their children will be dashed to pieces, and
        their pregnant women will be ripped open. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Return to Yahweh'
      title: Return to Yahweh
      number: 1
      content: 'Return to Yahweh your God, O Israel, for you have stumbled because
        of your sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Take words with you, and return to Yahweh. Say to him, \u201CTake
        away all guilt; accept good, and we will offer the fruit of our lips. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Assyria will not save us; we will not ride on horses,  and we will
        say no more, \u201COur God,\u201D to the work of our hands because in you
        the fatherless child finds mercy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will heal their disloyalty;  I will love them freely because my
        anger has turned back from them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I will be like the dew to Israel; he will blossom like the lily plant,
        and he will strike his roots like the trees of Lebanon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'His new plant shoots will spread out; his splendor will be like the
        olive tree, and his scent like the trees of Lebanon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They will again dwell in my shadow; they will grow grain and they
        will blossom like the plant vine; his fame will be like the wine of Lebanon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O Ephraim, what have I to do with idols? I myself have answered and
        looked after you.  I am like a luxuriant cypress; your fruit comes from me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Who is wise that he can understand these things? Who is discerning
        that he knows them? The ways of Yahweh are right, and the righteous walk
        in them; but transgressors stumble in them. '
      comments: []
